<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 5:33PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow bands expected this evening...
Rapidly changing conditions are expected this evening as a cold
front moves southward in into central and southwest Montana. Moderate
to heavy snow will develop along and behind the front. Rapid
reductions in visibility to 1/4 mile or less remain possible,
along with rapid freeze ups on area roadways.
The snow will likely reach the Helena area between 7 and 8 pm and
the Bozeman area by 10 pm. Moderate to heavy snow may linger
behind the initial band.</description>
